# ParkiPay Mobile — Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .env (same folder) and fill in ONE value below.
# NEVER commit .env to git — it is already in .gitignore.
#
# ── Which URL do I use? ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  Scenario A — Android EMULATOR (AVD) on same PC as backend:
#    Comment out EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL entirely.
#    The app auto-detects 10.0.2.2:8000 (AVD's alias for the host machine).
#
#  Scenario B — iOS SIMULATOR on same Mac as backend:
#    Comment out EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL entirely.
#    The app auto-detects localhost:8000.
#
#  Scenario C — Physical Android or iOS device (USB / Wi-Fi):
#    Find your PC/Mac LAN IP first:
#      macOS/Linux : ifconfig | grep "inet " | grep -v 127
#      Windows     : ipconfig | findstr "IPv4"
#      Termux      : ip addr show | grep "inet " | grep -v 127
#    Then set:
#      EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8000
#    Also make sure your PC firewall allows inbound TCP on port 8000.
#
#  Scenario D — Render (staging / production):
#    EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://parkipay-api.onrender.com
#    Note: free Render instances sleep after 15 min of inactivity.
#    The first login after idle may take 30–50 s while the server wakes up.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment and edit the line that matches your scenario:

# Scenario C — physical device (replace with your actual LAN IP):
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.42:8000

# Scenario D — Render production:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://parkipay-api.onrender.com
